: Wave is disturbance that transfer energy from one place to another without the actutal transfer of matter:

: Transverse wave: it is the wave in which particle vibrate perpendicular to the direction of wave movement: eg: water wave, electromagnetic wave

: Longitudnal wave: here particle wave and wave motion both are parllel to each other: sound wave : earthquake primary wave:

: compression : here the wave or very close to each ither and here the pressure is high:

: rarefraction: here the wave or not close to each other and they are spread out so this is known as rarefraction:

DIFFRENCE BETWEEN TRANSEVERSE AND LONGITUDNAL WAVE:

| Feature            | Transverse Wave                     | Longitudinal Wave         |
| ------------------ | ----------------------------------- | ------------------------- |
| Particle direction | Perpendicular                       | Parallel                  |
| Medium requirement | Solids & liquid surface             | Solids, liquids & gases   |
| Wave components    | Crests & troughs                    | Compression & rarefaction |
| Examples           | Light, water waves                  | Sound, slinky waves       |
| Wave type          | Often mechanical or electromagnetic | Mechanical only           |


