low freq: means sound is low:

loudness is measured in decibel:

| Property of Sound              | What it Means                   | Measured In                      |
| ------------------------------ | ------------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| **Frequency**                  | How many vibrations per second  | **Hertz (Hz)**                   |
| **Wavelength**                 | Length of one wave              | **Meter (m)**                    |
| **Speed of Sound**             | How fast sound travels          | **m/s** (meter/second)           |
| **Amplitude**                  | Maximum displacement            | **Meter (m)**                    |
| **Loudness / Intensity Level** | How loud the sound is           | **Decibel (dB)**                 |
| **Sound Intensity**            | Power per area                  | **W/mÂ²** (Watt per square meter) |
| **Time Period**                | Time for one complete vibration | **Seconds (s)**                  |


